der.com%2F6527d99d68f1d46f52afbc14%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221963%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFederal%20Reserve%20Chair%20Jerome.%3Cp%3EReuters%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%20%3Cli%3EThe%20Federal%20Reserve's%20economists%20are%20predicting%20a%20so-called%20Goldilocks%20scenario%2C%20Fed%20minutes%20show.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EThey%20expect%20growth%2C%20flat%20unemployment%2C%20and%20inflation%20to%20fall%20to%20around%202%25%20between%202024%20and%202026.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EFed%20staff%20don't%20anticipate%20a%20recession%20after%20raising%20it%20as%20a%20distinct%20possibility%20earlier%20this%20year.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20economy%20is%20likely%20headed%20for%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffed-reserve-economists-goldilocks-recession-inflation-economy-markets-powell-investors-2023-9%5C%22%3Eso-called%20Goldilocks%20scenario%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Federal%20Reserve's%20own%20economists.%20At%20the%20time%20of%20the%20central%20bank's%20September%20meeting%2C%20they%20predicted%20slower%20but%20still%20positive%20growth%2C%20roughly%20flat%20unemployment%2C%20and%20a%20drop%20in%20inflation%20to%20about%202%25%20over%20the%20next%20three%20years%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.federalreserve.gov%2Fmonetarypolicy%2Ffiles%2Ffomcminutes20230920.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eminutes%20released%20on%20Wednesday%20show%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20staff's%20forecast%20of%20continued%20economic%20expansion%2C%20no%20spike%20in%20joblessness%2C%20and%20the%20pace%20of%20price%20growth%20slowing%20to%20around%20the%20Fed's%20target%20level%20between%202024%20and%202026%20represents%20a%20real%20shift%20in%20sentiment%20from%20earlier%20this%20year.%20The%20latest%20minutes%20don't%20even%20mention%20recession%2C%20whereas%20the%20staff%20warned%20that%20was%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Ffed-economists-outlook-recession-stocks-real-estate-prices-inflation-unemployment-2023-2%5C%22%3Edistinct%20possibility%3C%2Fa%3E%20back%20in%20February.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmerica's%20economic%20strength%20has%20surprised%20many%20experts.%20Inflation%20soared%20as%20high%20as%209.1%25%20last%20summer%2C%20a%2040-year%20high%2C%20spurring%20the%20Fed%20to%20hike%20interest%20rates%20from%20nearly%20zero%20to%20north%20of%205%25%20in%20under%2018%20months.%20Higher%20rates%20can%20curb%20the%20pace%20of%20price%20increases%20by%20driving%20up%20borrowing%20costs%20and%20encouraging%20people%20to%20save%20instead%20of%20spend%2C%20but%20they%20can%20also%20erode%20demand%20so%20much%20that%20an%20economy%20sinks%20into%20recession%20and%20unemployment%20soars.%20There's%20also%20no%20guarantee%20they'll%20bring%20down%20inflation%2C%20which%20can%20be%20stubborn.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Fed%20staff%20noted%20their%20latest%20forecast%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffed-reserve-economists-goldilocks-recession-inflation-economy-markets-powell-investors-2023-9%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520Fed%2527s%2520own%2520economists%2520now%2Clow%2520inflation%252C%2520and%2520positive%2520growth%26amp%3Btext%3DEconomists%2520from%2520the%2520Federal%2520Reserve%2Cfor%2520a%2520soft%252Dlanding%2520scenario.%5C%22%3Eeven%20brighter%20than%20July's%20edition%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20as%20consumer%20and%20business%20spending%20have%20been%20more%20resilient%20to%20financial%20pressures%20than%20expected.%20They%20pointed%20to%20solid%20growth%20in%20the%20third%20quarter%2C%20a%20tight%20labor%20market%20with%20low%20unemployment%20and%20strong%20but%20slowing%20job%20gains%2C%20and%20signs%20of%20slowing%20inflation%20as%20reasons%20for%20their%20optimism.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20latest%20minutes%20may%20also%20reassure%20investors.%20Staff%20warned%20in%20February%20that%20the%20S%26amp%3BP%20500's%20forward%20multiple%20was%20above%20its%20med