ograms.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EBut%20they're%20unlikely%20to%20do%20that%20with%20Congress%20split.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20needs%20to%20deal%20with%20its%20soaring%20budget%20deficit%2C%20but%20the%20only%20options%20available%20for%20it%20to%20do%20so%20mean%20that%20it%20probably%20won't%2C%20according%20to%20Nobel%20laureate%20Paul%20Krugman.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20because%20the%20two%20paths%20to%20getting%20the%20deficit%20under%20control%20are%3A%20slash%20spending%20on%20social%20programs%2C%20or%20raise%20taxes.%20With%20a%20split%20Congress%2C%20neither%20are%20likely%20to%20happen.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3B%5BW%5Dhile%20we%20needn't%20panic%20over%20budget%20deficits%2C%20a%20lower%20deficit%20would%20really%20help%20with%20economic%20management%20right%20now.%20But%20it%20isn't%20going%20to%20happen%2C%26quot%3B%20Krugman%20said%20in%20an%20op-ed%20for%20the%20New%20York%20Times%20on%20Monday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Nobel%20economist%20pointed%20to%20the%20soaring%20cost%20of%20borrowing%20as%20rates%20rise.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20far%2C%20there's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fpaul-krugman-inflation-falling-no-sign-us-recession-2023-6%5C%22%3Eno%20evidence%20that%20high%20rates%20will%20push%20the%20economy%20into%20a%20recession%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Krugman%20said%2C%20but%20they%20do%20pose%20a%20problem%20down%20the%20road%20for%20the%20growing%20mountain%20of%20US%20debt%2C%20which%20just%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fbonds%2Ftreasury-yields-jump-us-debt-hits-record-33-trillion-2023-9%5C%22%3Enotched%20%2433%20trillion%20for%20the%20first%20time%20this%20year%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20Krugman%20doesn't%20believe%20the%20US%20is%20at%20risk%20for%20a%20fiscal%20crisis%20anytime%20soon%2C%20higher%20rates%20means%20it'll%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fbonds%2Fus-debt-c