%20he%20has%20emerged%20as%20%E2%80%9CIndia%E2%80%99s%20biggest%20private%20thermal%20power%20company%20and%20biggest%20private%20port%20operator.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EA%20US%20short-seller%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbusiness%2Fwhy-has-the-adani-hindenburg-issue-become-a-matter-of-national-concern%5C%22%3EHindenburg%20Research%E2%80%99s%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20January%20this%20year%20raised%20serious%20questions%20about%20several%20aspects%20of%20how%20Adani%20functioned%20which%20led%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbusiness%2Fadani-rise-reading-list%5C%22%3Eserious%20questions%3C%2Fa%3E%20arising%20globally%20about%20the%20group%20and%20also%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbusiness%2Fsebi-vinod-adani-free-float-rules%5C%22%3Eregulatory%20mechanisms%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20India.%20Stock%20market%20watchdog%20Securities%20and%20Exchange%20Board%20of%20India%20(SEBI)%20came%20under%20fire%20even%20when%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20expert%20committee%20pointed%20to%20certain%20changes%20in%20rules%20that%20may%20have%20made%20it%20easier%20for%20Adani%20to%20escape%20scrutiny.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fbecause-of-repealed-provisions-sebi-hit-opaque-structure-wall-while-investigating-adani-sc-panel%5C%22%3EBecause%20of%20Repealed%20Provisions%2C%20SEBI%20Hit%20%E2%80%98Opaque%20Structure%E2%80%99%20Wall%20While%20Investigating%20Adani%3A%20SC%20Panel%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAdani%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businesstoday.in%2Flatest%2Fcorporate%2Fstory%2Fadani-group-hits-out-at-financial-times-for-trying-to-tarnish-reputation-financially-destabilise-company-401342-2023-10-10%5C%22%3Ehas%20denied%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20charges%2C%20both%20those%20levelled%20by%20Hindenburg%20and%20then%20of%20coal%20import%20over-pricing%20by%20the%20%3Cem%3EFinancial%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20said%20it%20has%20been%20vindicated%20by%20the%20Directorate%20of%20Revenue%20Intelligence%20(DRI%E2%80%99s)%20decision%20this%20year%20to%20withdraw%20an%20appeal%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%20a%20case%20against%20one%20of%20the%2040%20importers%20named%20in%202016.%20It%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20issue%20of%20overvaluation%20in%20the%20import%20of%20coal%20was%20conclusively%20settled%20by%20India%E2%80%99s%20highest%20court%20of%20law.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EFT%3C%2Fem%3E%20cites%20the%20%E2%80%9Cunresolved%20nature%20of%20the%20DRI%20investigation%20and%20the%20apparent%20continuation%20of%20the%20alleged%20practices%E2%80%9D%20raising%20%E2%80%9Cfresh%20questions%20about%20the%20relationship%20between%20Adani%20and%20the%20administration%20of%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWatchdog%20SEBI%E2%80%99s%20role%20too%20has%20come%20in%20the%20limelight%20after%20it%20emerged%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscroll.in%2Farticle%2F1055231%2Fsebi-knew-about-allegations-against-adani-group-since-2014-letter-shows%5C%22%3Eit%20knew%20about%20allegations%20against%20Adani%20Group%20since%202014%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20a%20letter%20which%20was%20part%20of%20the%20OCCRP-%3Cem%3EFT-The%20Guardian%E2%80%99s%3C%2Fem%3E%20investigation%20showed.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20recent%20scandal%20to%20hit%20Adani%20were%20allegations%20that%20the%20chairman%20of%20SEBI%20at%20that%20time%20was%20%E2%80%9Cnow%20an%20independent%20director%20of%20Adani-owned%20NDTV.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EFinancial%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20raised%20three%20key%20points%20in%20its%20investigation%2C%20after%20looking%20at%2030%20shipments%20of%20coal%20from%20Indonesia%20to%20India%20by%20an%20Adani%20company%20over%2032%20months%20between%202019%20and%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Adani%20Group%20has%20rejected%20charges%20of%20wrongdoing.%20Adani%20has%20termed%20the%20investigation%20as%20being%20based%20on%20an%20%E2%80%9Cold%2C%20baseless%20allegation%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20is%20%E2%80%9Ca%20clever%20recycling%20and%20selective%20misrepresentation%20of%20publicly%20available%20facts%20and%20information.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EInflated%20prices%20of%20imported%20coal%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20inflation%20in%20imported%20coal%20that%20%3Cem%3EFT%3C%2Fem%3E%20alleges%20Adani%20has%20been%20doing%20may%20have%20sometimes%2C%20per%20the%20report%2C%20allowed%20it%20to%20make%2052%25%20profit%20margins%20in%20an%20industry%20where%20profit%20margins%20are%20otherwise%20considered%20low.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20all%20cases%20that%20%3Cem%3EFT%3C%2Fem%3E%20examined%2C%20it%20says%20%E2%80%9Cprices%20in%20import%20records%20were%20far%20higher%20than%20those%20in%20corresponding%20export%20declarations.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20journeys%2C%20from%20where%20they%20were%20imported%20back%20to%20a%20port%20in%20India%2C%20usually%20owned%20by%20Adani%2C%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20value%20of%20the%20combined%20shipments%20unaccountably%20increased%20by%20over%20%2470%20million.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAmong%20the%20specific%20instances%20the%20London-based%20financial%20daily%20has%20found%2C%20it%20says%20that%20in%20January%202019%2C%20coal%20meant%20for%20Adani%2C%20departed%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20Indonesian%20port%20of%20Kaliorang%20in%20East%20Kalimantan%20carrying%2074%2C820%20tonnes%20of%20thermal%20coal%20destined%20for%20the%20fires%20of%20an%20Indian%20power%20station.%20During%20the%20voyage%2C%20something%20extraordinary%20occurred%3A%20the%20value%20of%20its%20cargo%20doubled.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20%E2%80%9Cin%20export%20records%20the%20price%20was%20%241.9mn%2C%20plus%20%2442%2C000%20for%20shipping%20and%20insurance.%20On%20arrival%20at%20India%E2%80%99s%20largest%20commercial%20port%2C%20Mundra%20in%20Gujarat%20run%20by%20Adani%2C%20the%20declared%20import%20value%20was%20%244.3mn.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F05%2F29113309%2FAdani_Mundra_Port_Kutch_Gujarat1.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22792%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F05%2F29113309%2FAdani_Mundra_Port_Kutch_Gujarat1.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F05%2F29113309%2FAdani_Mundra_Port_Kutch_Gujarat1-300x200.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-254571%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22529%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThe%20inflation%20in%20imported%20coal%20that%20FT%20alleges%20Adani%20has%20been%20doing%20may%20have%20sometimes%2C%20per%20the%20report%2C%20allowed%20it%20to%20make%2052%25%20profit%20margins%20in%20an%20industry%20where%20profit%20margins%20are%20otherwise%20considered%20low.%20File%20image%20of%20the%20Adani%20Mundra%20port%20in%20Gujarat%E2%80%99s%20Kutch.%20Photo%3A%20Emperor%20Genius%20at%20English%20Wikipedia%2C%20CC%20BY-SA%203.0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20allowed%20for%20%E2%80%9C52%25%20profit%20margins%E2%80%9D%20as%20a%20result%20of%20over-invoicing%2C%20and%20leading%20to%20unusual%20profits.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%20%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3EAn%20FT%20analysis%20supports%20longstanding%20claims%20that%20Adani%20Group%20has%20been%20inflating%20fuel%20costs%20for%20billions%20of%20dollars%20of%20coal%2C%20leading%20to%20millions%20of%20Indians%20overpaying%20for%20electricity%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FJV2GlxrBx8%5C%22%3Ehttps%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FJV2GlxrBx8%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2Fv8wlKVQY3m%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2Fv8wlKVQY3m%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%94%20Financial%20Times%20(%40FT)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FFT%2Fstatus%2F1712384879499862070%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EOctober%2012%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EFT%3C%2Fem%3E%20says%20%E2%80%9Cannual%20profits%20at%20Adani%20Enterprises%20quadrupled%20over%20the%20past%20five%20years%2C%20to%20earnings%20before%20interest%2C%20tax%2C%20depreciation%20and%20amortisation%20of%20%241.2bn%20in%20the%20most%20recent%20financial%20year.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELittle-known%20middlemen%20companies%20used%20to%20import%20paid%20higher%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%C2%A0FT%3C%2Fem%3E%20says%20that%20Adani%20Enterprises%2C%20the%20group%E2%80%99s%20oldest%20and%20most%20valuable%20company%2C%20generates%20the%20lion%E2%80%99s%20share%20of%20its%20sales%20and%20profits%20from%20its%20coal%20trading%20division%20called%20Integrated%20Resources%20Management%20(IRM).%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20division%2C%20%E2%80%9Cboasts%20of%20its%20expertise%20in%20logistics%20and%20commodity%20trading%E2%80%9D%20based%20in%20four%20global%20offices%20and%2019%20Indian%20locations.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20most%20recent%20financial%20year%2C%20which%20ended%20in%20March%2C%20IRM%20reported%20trading%2088%20million%20tonnes%20of%20coal%2C%20says%20the%20news%20report.%20Its%20results%20for%20the%20final%20quarter%20of%20that%20year%2C%20the%20first%20set%20of%20accounts%20published%20after%20Hindenburg%E2%80%99s%20report%2C%20covered%20a%20three-month%20period%20when%20the%20market%20price%20of%20coal%20had%20halved.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EYet%2C%20notes%20%3Cem%3EFT%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CIRM%20thrived%2C%20delivering%20a%2024%25%20rise%20in%20earnings%20before%20tax%20and%20interest%20to%20Rs%208.3%20billion%20(%24101%20million)%2C%20on%20a%206%25%20rise%20in%20sales%20to%20Rs%20186%20billion%20(%242.3%20billion)%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20IRM%20did%20not%20make%20extraordinary%20profits.%20Three%20%E2%80%9Cmiddlemen%E2%80%9D%20companies%20it%20used%20to%20buy%20coal%20from%2C%20that%20supplied%20the%20Adani%20group%20with%20coal%2C%20appear%20to%20have%20made%20more%20substantial%20amounts%E2%80%9D.%20%3Cem%3EFT%3C%2Fem%3E%20identifies%20them%20as%20Hi%20Lingos%20in%20Taipei%2C%20Taurus%20Commodities%20General%20Trading%20in%20Dubai%2C%20and%20Pan%20Asia%20Tradelink%20in%20Singapore.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFor%2042%20million%20tonnes%20of%20coal%20supplied%20by%20its%20own%20operations%20in%20that%20time%2C%20the%20Adani%20group%20declared%20an%20average%20price%20of%20%24130%20per%20tonne.%20But%20for%20the%2031%20million%20tonnes%20of%20coal%20supplied%20by%20its%20three%20middlemen%2C%20the%20average%20price%20declared%20per%20tonne%20was%20%24155%2C%20per%20tonne.%20This%20was%20at%20a%20%E2%80%9C20%25%20premium%20worth%20almost%20%24800%20million.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EFT%3C%2Fem%3E%20identifies%20Hi%20Lingos%20as%20being%20owned%20by%20Chang%20Chung-Ling%2C%20a%20Taiwanese%20businessman%20previously%20%E2%80%9Cidentified%20by%20the%20%3Cem%3EFT%3C%2Fem%3E%20as%20a%20potentially%20controversial%20owner%20of%20Adani%20stock.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20middleman%20company%20Taurus%2C%20it%20says%2C%20is%20run%20from%20Dubai%20and%20whose%20ownership%20it%20was%20unable%20to%20conclusively%20establish.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20third%20company%2C%20Pan%20Asia%20Coal%20Trading%2C%20which%20%E2%80%9Cprimarily%20supplied%20Adani%20Power%20and%20did%20not%20have%20other%20Indian%20customers%20for%20coal%20in%20the%20records%20reviewed%20by%20the%20%3Cem%3EFT%3C%2Fem%3E.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESenior%20industry%20traders%20%3Cem%3EFT%3C%2Fem%3E%20spoke%20to%2C%20%E2%80%9Cquestioned%20the%20use%20of%20little-known%20trading%20houses%2C%20as%20large%20buyers%20of%20coal%20generally%20prefer%20to%20partner%20with%20big%20trading%20houses%20that%20have%20strong%20credit%20ratings%20and%20a%20reliable%20record%20for%20commodity%20deals%20involving%20the%20exchange%20of%20hundreds%20of%20millions%20of%20dollars.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EFT%3C%2Fem%3E%20does%20not%20rule%20out%20the%20possibility%20of%20higher%20quality%20coal%20in%20some%20cases%20leading%20to%20a%20marginally%20higher%20price%2C%20yet%2C%20it%20notes%20that%20Adani%20also%20appears%20to%20have%20supplied%20itself%20with%20%E2%80%9Cunusually%20expensive%20coal.%20For%20the%20508%20shipments%20with%20a%20calorific%20value%20where%20Adani%20companies%20were%20listed%20as%20both%20supplier%20and%20importer%2C%20most%20%E2%80%94%2087%25%20%E2%80%94%20were%20priced%20higher%20than%20the%20closest%20Argus%20benchmark%2C%20at%20a%20median%20premium%20of%2024%25.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EArgus%20is%20an%20independent%20provider%20of%20market%20intelligence%20to%20the%20global%20energy%20and%20commodity%20markets%2C%20and%20is%20treated%20as%20a%20provider%20of%20price%20benchmarks%20globally.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2017%2F10%2F1312074_Wallpaper2.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20coal%20ministry%20is%20discouraging%20generators%20from%20going%20for%20imports%20to%20meet%20their%20fuel%20shortages.%20Credit%3A%20PTI%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22904%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-189061%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22678%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EFor%2042%20million%20tonnes%20of%20coal%20supplied%20by%20its%20own%20operations%20in%20that%20time%2C%20the%20Adani%20group%20declared%20an%20average%20price%20of%20%24130%20per%20tonne.%20But%20for%20the%2031%20million%20tonnes%20of%20coal%20supplied%20by%20its%20three%20middlemen%2C%20the%20average%20price%20declared%20per%20tonne%20was%20%24155%2C%20per%20tonne.%20This%20was%20at%20a%20%E2%80%9C20%25%20premium%20worth%20almost%20%24800%20million.%E2%80%9D%20Credit%3A%20PTI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbusiness%2Fadanis-acquisitions-india-needs-to-keep-track-costs%5C%22%3EAdani%E2%80%99s%20Acquisitions%3A%20Why%20India%20Needs%20to%20Keep%20Track%20of%20the%20Costs%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPublic%20pays%20higher%20prices%20for%20power%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20other%20important%20implication%20of%20the%20allegedly%20overpriced%20coal%2C%20that%20the%20%3Cem%3EFT%3C%2Fem%3E%20investigation%20draws%20attention%20to%2C%20is%20the%20charge%20that%20these%20high%20costs%20translated%20directly%20into%20higher%20prices%20paid%20by%20consumers%2C%20especially%20in%20Gujarat%20where%20the%20opposition%20Congress%20party%20has%20already%20flagged%20the%20issue.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20August%20this%20year%2C%20opposition%20politicians%20in%20Gujarat%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fcities%2Fahmedabad%2Fcongress-accuses-guvnl-of-paying-rs-3900-cr-extra-to-adani-power-govt-says-misleading-8911127%2F%5C%22%3Eaccused%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20state%20government%20of%20making%20almost%20%24500%20million%20in%20excess%20payments%20to%20Adani%20Power%20over%20five%20years%20under%20a%20power%20purchase%20agreement%20linked%20to%20the%20price%20of%20coal.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20opposition%20claimed%20a%20letter%20from%20the%20state%20power%20utility%20GUVNL%20showed%20it%20had%20paid%20the%20sums%20to%20Adani%20for%20coal%20procured%20at%20premium%20prices%2C%20and%20that%20%E2%80%9CAdani%20had%20not%20provided%20paperwork.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CGUVNL%20paid%20Rs%2013%2C802%20crore%20(%242%20billion)%20as%20energy%20charges%20to%20the%20company.%20But%20if%20coal%20rates%20as%20per%20Argus%20index%20is%20taken%20into%20consideration%2C%20then%20only%20Rs%209%2C902%20crore%20(%241.5%20billion)%20should%20have%20been%20paid%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20opposition%20leader%20is%20quoted%20as%20saying.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20then%2C%20notes%20%3Cem%3EFT%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20said%20that%20the%20payments%20