0hoping%20talks%20at%20Stellantis%20today%20are%20more%20productive%20than%20Ford%20yesterday%2C%26quot%3B%20Fain%20wrote%20on%20X%2C%20formerly%20Twitter%2C%20without%20saying%20what%20might%20happen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFord's%20truck%20plant%20makes%20heavy-duty%20F-Series%20pickup%20trucks%20and%20large%20Ford%20and%20Lincoln%20SUVs%2C%20hitting%20the%20company's%20most%20lucrative%20products.%20The%20vehicles%20made%20at%20the%20plant%20generate%20%2425%20billion%20per%20year%20in%20revenue%2C%20the%20company%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFain%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20that%20the%20union%20has%20waited%20long%20enough%20%26quot%3Bbut%20Ford%20hasn't%20gotten%20the%20message%26quot%3B%20to%20bargain%20for%20a%20fair%20contract.%20%26quot%3BIf%20they%20can't%20understand%20that%20after%20four%20weeks%2C%20the%208%2C700%20workers%20shutting%20down%20this%20extremely%20profitable%20plant%20will%20help%20them%20understand%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Fain%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20strike%20came%20nearly%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fuaw-auto-union-strike-could-change-industry-forever-2023-9%5C%22%3Efour%20weeks%20after%20the%20union%20began%20its%20walkouts%20against%20General%20Motors%2C%20Ford%20and%20Stellantis%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20Sept.%2015%2C%20with%20one%20assembly%20plant%20from%20each%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%2C%20however%2C%20called%20the%20strike%20expansion%20%26quot%3Bgrossly%20irresponsible%26quot%3B%20and%20said%20it%20has%20made%20strong%20wage%20and%20benefit%20offers%20to%20the%20union.%20It%20said%20the%20move%20puts%20about%20a%20dozen%20other%20Ford%20facilities%20at%20risk%2C%20as%20well%20as%20parts%20supply%20plants%20that%20together%20employ%20over%20100%2C000%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Ford%20executive%20said%20the%20union%20called%20a%20meeting%20at%20the%20company's%20Dearborn%2C%20Michigan%2C%20headquarters%20Wednesday%20afternoon%20where%20Fain%20asked%20if%20the%20company%20had%20another%20offer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHigh-ranking%20Ford%20executives%20responded%20that%20they%20are%20working%20on%20possibly%20bringing%20electric%20vehicle%20battery%20plants%20into%20the%20UAW%20national%20contract%2C%20essentially%20making%20them%20unionized.%20But%20they%20didn't%20have%20a%20significantly%20different%20economic%20offer%2C%20the%20executive%20said.%20Fain%20was%20told%20the%20company%20put%20a%20strong%20offer%20on%20the%20table%2C%20but%20there%20wasn't%20a%20lot%20of%20room%20to%20increase%20it%20and%20keep%20it%20affordable%20for%20the%20business%2C%20the%20executive%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFain%20responded%20by%20saying%2C%20if%20that's%20the%20company's%20best%20offer%2C%20%26quot%3BYou%20just%20lost%20Kentucky%20Truck%20Plant%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20the%20executive.%20The%20meeting%20only%20lasted%20about%2015%20minutes%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20video%2C%20Fain%20said%20the%20union%20moved%20because%20Ford%20didn't%20change%20its%20offer.%20%26quot%3BWe've%20been%20very%20patient%20working%20with%20the%20company%20on%20this%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey%20have%20not%20met%20expectations%2C%20they're%20not%20even%20coming%20to%20the%20table%20on%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20escalation%20against%20Ford%20shows%20that%20Fain%20is%20trying%20to%20increase%20pressure%20on%20the%20company%2C%20said%20Marick%20Masters%2C%20a%20business%20professor%20at%20Wayne%20State%20University%20who%20follows%20labor%20issues.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Ford%20and%20the%20other%20automakers%20have%20made%20concessions%20and%20raised%20wage%20offers%2C%20he%20said.%20The%20companies%2C%20he%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bmay%20have%20reached%20their%20resistance%20points%20to%20varying%20degrees.%26quot%3B%20Executives%2C%20he%20said%2C%20have%20bottom-line%20positions%20they%20can't%20cross%20in%20terms%20of%20staying%20competitive%20with%20other%20automakers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFain%2C%20Masters%20said%2C%20likely%20is%20testing%20how%20far%20he%20needs%20to%20push%20Ford%20before%20going%20to%20%26quot%3Bfull%20throttle%2C%26quot%3B%20by%20taking%20all%2057%2C000%20Ford%20members%20out%20on%20strike.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20union's%20move%20doesn't%20leave%20him%20optimistic%20for%20a%20quick%20end%20to%20the%20strikes%2C%20Masters%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20the%20issues%20that%20remain%20on%20the%20table%20are%20quite%20thorny%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20pointing%20to%20union%20demands%20that%20all%20workers%20get%20defined%20benefit%20pensions%20and%20health%20insurance%20when%20they%20retire.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20UAW%20expanded%20its%20strikes%20on%20Sept.%2022%2C%20adding%2038%20GM%20and%20Stellantis%20parts%20warehouses.%20Assembly%20plants%20from%20Ford%20and%20GM%20were%20added%20the%20week%20after%20that.%20The%20Kentucky%20strike%20brings%20to%2033%2C700%20the%20number%20of%20workers%20on%20strike%20against%20the%20three%20automakers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThus%20far%2C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fuaw-auto-union-strike-strategy-longer-walkouts-2023-9%5C%22%3Ethe%20union%20has%20decided%20to%20target%20a%20small%20number%20of%20plants%20from%20each%20company%3C%2Fa%3E%20rather%20than%20have%20all%20146%2C000%20UAW%20members%20at%20the%20automakers%20go%20on%20strike%20at%20the%20same%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20week%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapnews.com%2Farticle%2Fauto-workers-strike-general-motors-battery-plants-a6ad7d6b9c3f42c24f3c7dbe21f4b694%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20union%20reported%20progress%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0in%20the%20talks%20and%20decided%20not%20to%20add%20any%20more%20plants.%20This%20came%20after%20GM%20agreed%20to%20bring%20joint-venture%20electric%20vehicle%20battery%20factories%20into%20the%20national%20master%20contract%2C%20almost%20assuring%20that%20the%20plants%20will%20be%20unionized.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBattery%20plants%20are%C2%A0a%20major%20point%20of%20contention%C2%A0in%20the%20negotiations.%20The%20UAW%20wants%20those%20plants%20to%20be%20unionized%20to%20assure%20jobs%20and%20top%20wages%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fuaw-strike-inexorable-math-electric-vehicles-elon-musk-tesla-ford-2023-9%5C%22%3Eworkers%20who%20will%20be%20displaced%20by%20the%20industry's%20ongoing%20transition%20to%20electric%20vehicles.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20the%20start%20of%20the%20strike%2C%20the%20three%20Detroit%20automakers%20have%20laid%20off%20roughly%204%2C800%20workers%20at%20factories%20that%20are%20not%20among%20the%20plants%20that%20have%20been%20hit%20by%20the%20UAW%20strikes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20companies%20say%20the%20strikes%20have%20forced%20them%20to%20impose%20those%20layoffs.%20They%20note%20that%20the%20job%20cuts%20have%20occurred%20mainly%20at%20factories%20that%20make%20parts%20for%20assembly%20plants%20that%20were%20closed%20by%20strikes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20UAW%20rejects%20that%20argument.%20It%20contends%20that%20the%20layoffs%20are%20unjustified%20and%20were%20imposed%20as%20part%20of%20the%20companies'%20pressure%20campaign%20to%20persuade%20UAW%20members%20to%20accept%20less%20in%20negotiations%20with%20automakers.%20The%20factories%20affected%20by%20layoffs%20are%20in%20six%20states%3A%20Michigan%2C%20Ohio%2C%20Illinois%2C%20Kansas%2C%20Indiana%20and%20New%20York.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESam%20Fiorani%2C%20an%20analyst%20with%20AutoForecast%20Solutions%2C%20a%20consulting%20firm%2C%20said%20he%20thinks%20the%20layoffs%20reflect%20a%20simple%20reality%3A%20The%20automakers%20are%20losing%20money%20because%20of%20the%20strikes.%20By%20slowing%20or%20idling%20factories%20that%20are%20running%20below%20their%20capacities%20because%20of%20strike-related%20parts%20shortages%2C%20Fiorani%20said%2C%20the%20companies%20can%20mitigate%20further%20losses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20doesn't%20make%20sense%20to%20keep%20running%20at%2030%25%20or%2040%25%20of%20capacity%20when%20it%20normally%20runs%2