20more%20in%20New%20York.%20Shares%20opened%20at%20%2441%20on%20Wednesday%2C%2011%25%20below%20their%20offer%20price%20of%20%2446.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthe-history-growth-of-birkenstock-german-shoe-brand-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enearly%20250-year-old%20company%3C%2Fa%3E%20listed%20on%20the%20New%20York%20Stock%20Exchange%20via%20an%20IPO%2C%20trading%20under%20the%20ticker%20%26quot%3BBIRK%26quot%3B%20and%20pushing%20up%20the%20fortunes%20of%20Alex%20and%20Christian%20Birkenstock.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInsider%20has%20approached%20the%20company%20for%20comment%20on%20Alex%20and%20Christian%20Birkenstock's%20net%20worth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20brothers%20became%20involved%20in%20the%20family%20sandal%20business%20%E2%80%94%20which%20traces%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.birkenstock-group.com%2Fde%2Fen%2Fabout-us%2Ftradition-since-1774%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eorigins%3C%2Fa%3E%20back%20to%20rural%20central%20Germany%20in%201774%20%E2%80%94%20as%20teenagers%20in%20the%201980s%20and%20were%20later%20joined%20by%20their%20old%20brother%20Stephan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202002%2C%20their%20father%2C%20Karl%20Birkenstock%2C%20stepped%20down%20and%20transferred%20management%20to%20the%20brothers.%20Around%20a%20decade%20later%2C%20the%20Birkenstock%20family%20gave%20up%20control%2C%20became%20a%20corporation%2C%20and%20appointed%20co-CEOs%2C%20its%20first%20non-family%20leaders.%20Stephan%20sold%20his%20shares%2C%20Bloomberg%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlex%20and%20Christian%20Birkenstock%2C%20who%20prior%20to%20then%20had%20been%20the%20ultimate%20controlling%20parties%20of%20the%20company%2C%20sold%20a%20majority%20stake%20to%20private-equity%20firm%20L%20Catterton%20in%202021%20in%20a%20deal%20that%20valued%20Birkenstock%20at%20%244.9%20billion.%20The%20brothers%20netted%20more%20than%20%E2%82%AC3%20billion%20(%243.2%20billion)%20from%20that%20transaction%2C%20Bloomberg%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20then%2C%20Christian%20Birkenstock%20retained%20a%20minority%20stake%20in%20the%20company%20and%20has%20got%20a%20return%20of%20more%20than%20100%25%2C%20Bloomberg%20reported%2C%20while%20Alex%20Birkenstock%20is%20no%20longer%20a%20listed%20shareholder.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EL%20Catterton%20is%20backed%20by%20billionaire%20Bernard%20Arnault's%20luxury%20conglomerate%20LVMH.%20In%20an%20October%20filing%2C%20Birkenstock%20named%20his%20son%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Falexandre-arnault-profile-tiffany-rimowa-lvmh-2021-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EAlexandre%20Arnault%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20to%20the%20company's%20board%20of%20directors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Bloomberg%2C%20the%20brothers'%20combined%20wealth%20places%20them%20on%20the%20Bloomberg%20Billionaires%20Index.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fbillionaires%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThey%20are%20not%20within%20the%20top%20500%20people%20on%20the%20list%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20who%20are%20listed%20publicly%20online%2C%20with%20the%20500th%20wealthiest%20person%20on%20that%20list%2C%20Charles%20Dolan%2C%20being%20worth%20over%20%245%20billion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EKendall%20Jenner%20made%20the%20shoes%20cool%2C%20while%20'Barbie'%20mocked%20them%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBirkenstock%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sec.gov%2FArchives%2Fedgar%2Fdata%2F1977102%2F000119312523233488%2Fd541624df1.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20it%20sold%20about%2030%20million%20units%20in%202022%2C%20with%20revenues%20of%201.24%20billion%20euros%20(%241.32%20billion).%20Direct-to-customer%20sales%20made%20up%2038%25%20of%20revenues%20in%20fiscal%202022%2C%20up%20from%2018%25%20in%20fiscal%202018%2C%20which%20it%20said%20was%20mainly%20because%20of%20e-commerce%20growth.%20The%20company%20has%20about%2045%20stores%2C%20nearly%20half%20of%20which%20are%20in%20Germany%2C%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sec.gov%2FArchives%2Fedgar%2Fdata%2F1977102%2F000119312523233488%2Fd541624df1.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIPO%20prospectus%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20it%20said%20that%2072%25%20of%20its%20customers%20were%20female%2C%20more%20than%20half%20of%20its%20revenues%20came%20from%20the%20Americas%2C%20and%20more%20than%20a%20third%20came%20from%20Europe.%20Baby%20boomers%2C%20millennials%2C%20and%20Gen%20Xers%20each%20accounted%20for%20around%2030%25%20of%20its%20customers%2C%20with%20Gen%20Zers%20making%20up%20just%2012%25%2C%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBirkenstock's%20IPO%20prospectus%20details%20how%20over%20the%20years%20the%20sandals%20became%20a%20mainstay%20for%20various%20groups%20%E2%80%93%20hippies%20in%20the%201960s%20and%201970s%2C%20eco-conscious%20people%20in%20the%201980s%2C%20and%20women%20in%20the%201990s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222556%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20Birkenstock%20shoe%20in%20%26quot%3BBarbie.%26quot%3B%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64baf05d5adc5f001951bfeb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221276%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBirkenstocks%20feature%20in%20Greta%20Gerwig's%20%26quot%3BBarbie.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3EWarner%20Bros.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20German%20orthopedic%20brand%2C%20long%20mocked%20as%20producing%20%26quot%3Bugly%26quot%3B%20shoes%2C%20has%20became%20a%20status%20symbol%20in%20recent%20years.%20Celebrities%20including%20Kendall%20Jenner%20and%20YouTuber%20Emma%20Chamberlain%20wore%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbirkenstock-boston-tiktok-trend-leads-to-high-resale-prices-2022-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%24160%20Boston%20clog%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20subsequently%20sold%20out%2C%20and%20its%20sandals%20featured%20in%20Greta%20Gerwig's%20blockbuster%20%26quot%3BBarbie%26quot%3B%20as%20a%20symbol%