245%2FF8KgdHwaEAAXScv.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EChandigarh%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20overlapping%20visits%20of%20Indian%20defence%20minister%20Rajnath%20Singh%20to%20Paris%20and%20that%20of%20France%E2%80%99s%20Dassault%20Aviation%20head%20Eric%20Trappier%20to%20New%20Delhi%20this%20week%20is%20an%C2%A0%20indication%20of%20the%20augmented%20level%20of%20bilateral%20military%20commerce%2C%20especially%20of%20combat%20aircraft%2C%20between%20the%20two%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20Singh%E2%80%99s%20October%2010-12%20trip%20to%20Italy%20and%20France%20focused%2C%20in%20the%20latter%20instance%2C%20on%20possible%20collaborations%20with%20its%20military-industrial%20complex%20to%20further%20India%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98Atmanirbharta%E2%80%99%20initiative%20to%20reduce%20materiel%20imports%2C%20Trappier%E2%80%99s%20Delhi%20visit%2C%20between%20October%209-10%2C%20was%20focused%20on%20supplying%20the%20Indian%20Navy%2026%20Rafale-M%20(Maritime)%20fighters%20for%20embarkation%20on%20%3Cem%3EINS%20Vikrant%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20its%20newly%20commissioned%20aircraft%20carrier.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccompanied%20by%20senior%20Dassault%20executive%20Richard%20Lavaud%2C%20Trappier%20is%20believed%20to%20have%20held%20talks%20with%20top%20defence%20and%20foreign%20ministry%20officials%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20Indian%20Air%20Force%20(IAF)%20and%20Indian%20Navy%20chiefs%20of%20staff%2C%20in%20which%20the%20delivery%20of%2022%20twin-engine%2C%20canard%20delta-wing%20Rafale-M%20fighters%20and%20four%20dual-seat%20trainers%20featured%20prominently.%20However%2C%20no%20official%20statement%20on%20these%20meetings%20have%2C%20so%20far%2C%20been%20provided.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F12153612%2FF8KgdH2aUAAcLfl.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F12153612%2FF8KgdH2aUAAcLfl.jpeg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F12153612%2FF8KgdH2aUAAcLfl-300x165.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F12153612%2FF8KgdH2aUAAcLfl-1024x561.jpeg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-679728%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22658%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ERajnath%20Singh%20with%20the%20CEOs%20of%20the%20top%20French%20defence%20companies%20including%20Eric%20Trappier%2C%20CEO%20of%20Dassault%2C%20Pierre%20Eric%20Pommellet%2C%20CEO%20of%20Naval%20Group%2C%20Guillaume%20Faury%2C%20CEO%20of%20Airbus%2C%20and%20Olivier%20Andries%2C%20CEO%20of%20Safran%20Group.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EDassault%20is%20also%20a%20frontrunner%20for%20the%20IAF%E2%80%99s%20long-pending%20requirement%20for%20114%20multi-role%20fighter%20aircraft%20(MRFA)%20with%20its%20Rafale.%20In%202016%2C%20India%20bought%2036%20via%20an%20inter-governmental%20agreement%20or%20IGA%20for%20around%20%249%20billion%20and%20divided%20them%20between%20two%20squadrons%20at%20Ambala%20and%20Hasimara%20Air%20Force%20Stations.%20Further%20strengthening%20Dassault%E2%80%99s%20credentials%20for%20the%20MRFA%20buy%20was%20the%20fact%20that%20it%20had%20already%20established%20a%20Rafale%20flight%20training%20and%20maintenance%2C%20repair%20and%20overhaul%20facility%20at%20Ambala%2C%20which%20would%20go%20a%20long%20way%20towards%20reducing%20overall%20costs%20for%20all%20further%20similar%20fighter%20buys.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAnd%2C%20more%20importantly%2C%20acquiring%20tried%20and%20tested%20Rafales%20would%20also%20hasten%20fighter%20inductions%20by%20dispensing%20with%20extended%20trials%2C%20to%20speedily%20boost%20the%20IAFs%20declining%20fighter%20squadrons%2C%20which%20had%20depreciated%20to%2029-30%2C%20from%20a%20sanctioned%20strength%20of%2042%20squadrons.%20Additionally%2C%20industry%20officials%20said%20acquiring%20supplementary%20Rafales%20would%20also%20streamline%20the%20IAFs%20diverse%20fighter%20catalogue%2C%20which%20presently%20features%20seven%20different%20aircraft%20types%2C%20sustaining%20all%20of%20which%20was%20not%20only%20an%20enduring%20logistical%20nightmare%2C%20but%20also%20a%20hugely%20expensive%20affair%20for%20the%20financially%20overstretched%20force.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20IAF%20has%20had%20a%20long-established%20association%20with%20Dassault%2C%20which%20began%20in%201953%20with%20the%20arrival%20at%20Ambala%20of%20the%20first%20of%20some%20104%20of%20its%20MD%20450%20Ouragan%20fighter-bombers.%20Renamed%20Toofani%20%E2%80%93%20a%20direct%20translation%20from%20the%20aircraft%E2%80%99s%20French%20name%2C%20meaning%20Hurricane%20and%20also%20because%20Ouragan%20was%20difficult%20for%20IAF%20technicians%20and%20other%20personnel%20to%20pronounce%20%E2%80%93%20these%20fighters%20remained%20in%20service%20till%20the%20mid-1960%E2%80%99s%20and%20continued%20thereafter%20as%20advanced%20trainers%20and%20as%20target%20tugs.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fdefence-ties-serve-as-the-basic-pillar-of-india-france-bilateral-relations-modi%5C%22%3EIndia%2C%20France%20Announce%20Deals%20for%20Submarines%20and%20Jet%20Engines%2C%20but%20Silent%20on%20Rafale%20Naval%20Jets%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Toofanis%20%E2%80%93%20of%20which%2033%20were%20acquired%20in%20refurbished%20condition%20%E2%80%93%20were%20replaced%201957%20onwards%20by%20an%20equal%20number%20of%20Dassault%20Mystere%20IVA%E2%80%99s%20which%20were%20the%20first%20transonic%20aircraft%2C%20powered%20by%20Rolls-Royce%20Tay%20turbojets%2C%20to%20be%20commissioned%20into%20the%20French%20Air%20Force%20in%20the%20early%201950s.%20The%20IAF%20employed%20the%20Mystere%E2%80%99s%20extensively%20in%20the%201965%20war%20with%20Pakistan%20and%20in%20a%20limited%20role%20during%20the%20subsequent%201971%20operations%2C%20before%20eventually%20retiring%20them%20in%201973.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAfter%20a%20hiatus%20of%20a%20little%20over%20a%20decade%2C%20the%20IAF%20began%20inducting%20some%2050-odd%20Mirage-2000Hs%20(Hindustan%E2%80%99s)%20in%201986%2C%20which%20are%20presently%20being%20upgraded%20by%20Hindustan%20Aeronautics%20Limited%20(HAL)%20in%20Bangalore%20via%20a%20transfer%20of%20technology%20from%20Dassault%20under%20a%20%242.5%20billion%20contract%20signed%20in%202011.%20This%20retrofit%20was%20scheduled%20for%20completion%20by%20end-2021%2C%20but%20has%20been%20delayed%20and%20awaits%20conclusion.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Mirage-2000Hs%20were%2C%20in%20turn%20followed%20up%20with%2036%20Rafales%2C%20including%20six%20twin-seat%20trainers%2C%20all%20of%20which%20had%20been%20commissioned%20into%20service%20by%20late%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F01%2F11174740%2FDassault_Rafale_M_of_Flottille_17F_lands_aboard_USS_George_H.W._Bush_CVN-77_in_the_Atlantic_Ocean_on_10_May_2018_180510-N-UV609-0540.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F01%2F11174740%2FDassault_Rafale_M_of_Flottille_17F_lands_aboard_USS_George_H.W._Bush_CVN-77_in_the_Atlantic_Ocean_on_10_May_2018_180510-N-UV609-0540.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F01%2F11174740%2FDassault_Rafale_M_of_Flottille_17F_lands_aboard_USS_George_H.W._Bush_CVN-77_in_the_Atlantic_Ocean_on_10_May_2018_180510-N-UV609-0540-300x150.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F01%2F11174740%2FDassault_Rafale_M_of_Flottille_17F_lands_aboard_USS_George_H.W._Bush_CVN-77_in_the_Atlantic_Ocean_on_10_May_2018_180510-N-UV609-0540-1024x513.jpg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F01%2F11174740%2FDassault_Rafale_M_of_Flottille_17F_lands_aboard_USS_George_H.W._Bush_CVN-77_in_the_Atlantic_Ocean_on_10_May_2018_180510-N-UV609-0540-800x400.jpg%20800w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-575273%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22601%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ERepresentative%20image%20of%20a%20Rafale%20Marine%20aircraft.%20Photo%3A%20By%20US%20Navy%2FWikimedia%20Commons%2C%20Public%20Domain%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EIndustry%20officials%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20indicated%20that%20Trappier%20was%20eyeing%20the%20IAFs%20MRFA%20procurement%20that%20envisages%20importing%20a%20squadron%20of%2018%20shortlisted%20fighters%20in%20flyaway%20condition%20from%20amongst%20seven%20models%20on%20offer%20from%20overseas%20original%20equipment%20manufacturers%20(OEMs)%2C%20in%20response%20to%20the%20forces%20April%202018%20request%20for%20information.%20The%20remaining%2096%20platforms%20would%20be%20built%20indigenously%2C%20via%20a%20collaborative%20venture%20between%20the%20qualified%20OEM%20and%20a%20domestic%20strategic%20partner%20from%20either%20the%20private%20or%20public%20sector%2C%20with%20progressively%20enhanced%20levels%20of%20indigenisation%2C%20in%20the%20deal%2C%20estimated%20at%20around%20%2425%20billion.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20MRFA%20tender%20is%20expected%20imminently%2C%20industry%20sources%20said%2C%20and%20senior%20IAF%20officers%20estimate%20that%20these%20numbers%20could%20increase%20to%20around%20200%20units%2C%20in%20addition%20to%20possible%20export%20options%2C%20resulting%20in%20the%20platforms%20cost%20amortisation.%20Recent%20media%20reports%2C%20quoting%20official%20sources%2C%20revealed%20that%20even%20though%20the%20IAF%20planned%20on%20inducting%20some%20180%20variants%20of%20the%20indigenously%20developed%20Tejas%20Light%20Combat%20Aircraft%20to%20replace%20legacy%20fighters%20like%20the%20ground%20attack%20MiG-21s%20and%20SEPECAT%20Jaguars%2C%20the%20MRFA%20acquisition%20remained%20%E2%80%98on%20stream%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20six%20other%20OEMs%2C%20besides%20Dassault%2C%20who%20had%20responded%20to%20the%20IAF%E2%80%99s%20request%20for%20information%20include%20Eurofighter%20(Typhoon)%2C%20Sweden%E2%80%99s%20Saab%20(Gripen-E)%2C%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20United%20Aircraft%20Corporation%20and%20Sukhoi%20Corporation%20(MiG-35%20%E2%80%98Fulcrum-F%E2%80%99%20and%20Su-35%E2%80%99%20Flanker-E%E2%80%99)%20and%20the%20US%E2%80%99s%20%C2%A0Boeing%20and%20Lockheed%20Martin%20(F%2FA-18%20and%20F-15EX%20and%20the%20upgraded%20F-21).%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20in%20view%20of%20the%20ongoing%20war%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20evaluating%20the%20two%20Russian%20fighter%20types%20for%20eventual%20IAF%20acquisition%20was%2C%20justifiably%20irrational%2C%20considering%20the%20grave%20spares%20and%20components%20crisis%20the%20force%20is%20facing%20with%20regard%20to%20its%20fleet%20of%20some%20260%20multi-role%20Sukhoi-30%20MKI%E2%80%99s%20and%2050-odd%20upgraded%20MiG-29M%20fighter-bombers.%20At%20his%20annual%20press%20conference%20last%20week%20Air%20Chief%20Marshal%20V.R.%20Chaudhuri%20declared%20that%20the%20IAF%20planned%20on%20locally%20upgrading%2084%20of%20its%20260-odd%20Su-30MKI%E2%80%99s%20to%20%E2%80%98Super%20Sukhoi%E2%80%99%20status%20for%20Rs%2060%2C000%20crore%2C%20a%20venture%20that%20had%20earlier%20focused%20heavily%20on%20direct%20Russian%20involvement.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAlternately%2C%20shortlisting%20the%20Typhoon%20would%20only%20mean%20adding%20to%20the%20IAFs%20massive%20continuing%20logistic%20challenges%2C%20whilst%20the%20US%E2%80%99s%20F-18%20and%20the%20F-16%20%E2%80%93%20a%20precursor%20to%20the%20F-21%2C-had%20both%20been%20rejected%20by%20the%20IAF%20on%20multiple%20capability%20counts%20during%20trials%20conducted%202010%20onwards%20for%20the%20binned%20Medium%20Multi-Role%20Combat%20Aircraft%20contract%20floated%20in%202007.%20Saab%E2%80%99s%20Gripen-E%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20was%20a%20single-engine%20platform%2C%20and%20though%20the%20MRFA%20request%20for%20information%20had%20not%20specified%20any%20preference%20for%20single%20or%20dual%20power%20packs%2C%20the%20IAFs%20intrinsic%20preference%20for%20the%20latter%20remains%20unstated.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Findian-navy-rafale-deal-paris-bastille-day-modi%5C%22%3EIs%20There%20a%20Link%20Between%20Indian%20Navy%E2%80%99s%20Rafale-M%20Deal%20and%20the%20Paris%20Bastille%20Day%20Invite%20to%20Modi%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHence%2C%20by%20a%20process%20of%20elimination%2C%20the%20Rafale%20was%20more%20than%20favourably%20placed%20in%20the%20MRFA%20sweepstakes%2C%20due%20not%20only%20to%20its%20operational%20superiority%20over%20its%20competitors%20as%20acknowledged%20by%20the%20IAF%20%E2%80%93%20and%20now%20by%20the%20IN%20but%20also%20the%20host%20of%20multiple%20ancillary%20factors%20enumerated%20earlier.%20Besides%2C%20with%2026%20Rafale-M%20under%20purchase%2C%20that%20would%20make%20it%20an%20aggregate%20of%2062%20French%20fighters%20in%20service%20with%20the%20Indian%20military.%20Adding%20to%20these%20numbers%2C%20a%20cross-section%20of%20veterans%20said%2C%20made%20%E2%80%98eminent%E2%80%99%20commercial%2C%20logistical%20and%20operational%20sense.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMoreover%2C%20there%20was%20also%20the%20abandoned%20contractual%20template%20for%20the%20terminated%20Medium%20Multi-Role%20Combat%20Aircraft%20tender%20which%2C%20industry%20officials%20said%2C%20could%20easily%20be%20%E2%80%98tweaked%E2%80%99%20to%20suit%20an%20analogous%20MRFA%20purchase%20by%20resolving%20earlier%20glitches%20that%20would%20significantly%20compress%20negotiations.%20These%20earlier%20anomalies%20had%20centred%20on%20insistence%20by%20the%20MoD%20that%20Dassault%2C%20which%20was%20eventually%20shortlisted%2C%20shoulder%20eventual%20quality%20control%20responsibility%20for%20the%20108%20Rafales%20licence-built%20by%20HAL.%20This%20unwarranted%20conditionality%20had%20allegedly%20emerged%20as%20the%20deal-breaker%20for%20the%20Medium%20Multi-Role%20Combat%20Aircraft%20deal%20led%20to%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Defence%20procuring%20just%2036%20Rafales%20in%20fly-away%20condition%2C%20according%20to%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20account.%20Of%20course%2C%20what%20was%20left%20unexplained%20was%20why%2C%20on%20the%20eve%20of%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20visit%20to%20France%20in%202015%20(when%20the%20126%20jet%20co-production%20deal%20was%20scrapped%20in%20favour%20of%20buying%2036%20outright)%2C%20both%20Dassault%20and%20HAL%20had%20said%20they%20had%20ironed%20out%20their%20differences.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20Indian%20diplomats%2C%20security%20officials%20and%20analysts%20say%C2%A0it%20is%20less%20%E2%80%98arduous%E2%80%99%20conducting%20materiel%20commerce%20with%20Paris%20than%20with%20Washington%2C%20as%20the%20former%20is%20more%20flexible%20and%20pragmatic%20than%20the%20latter%2C%20especially%20with%20regard%20to%20transferring%20hi-tech%20military%20knowhow%20and%20passing%20on%20source-codes%20that%20manage%20fighter%20weapon%20and%20flight%20control%20systems.%20The%20US%2C%20for%20its%20part%2C%20remains%C2%A0constrained%C2%A0by%20rigid%20export%20regulations%20in%20this%20regard%20and%20hidebound%20by%20personal%20political%20and%20diplomatic%20considerations%20over%20platform%20deployments.%20France%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20is%20more%20%E2%80%98relaxed%E2%80%99%20on%20all%20these%20counts%2C%20displaying%20a%20Gallic%20%3Cem%3Esavoir%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3Efaire%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20strategically%20suits%20India%2C%20even%20if%20its%20equipment%20ends%20up%20being%20relatively%20more%20expensive.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697105702000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F12153245%2FF8KgdHwaEAAXScv.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Ffrance-us-fighter-jet-dassault-tech-rafale%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Today%2C%20Indian%20diplomats%2C%20security%20officials%20and%20analysts%20say%C2%A0it%20is%20less%20%E2%80%98arduous%E2%80%99%20conducting%20materiel%20commerce%20with%20Paris%20than%20with%20Washington.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Ffrance-us-fighter-jet-dassault-tech-rafale%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%26quot%3BPutting%20Child%20To%20Death%20Through%20Court%3F%26quot%3B%20Chief%20Justice%20In%20Abortion%20Case%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EIn%20strong%20observations%20while%20hearing%20a%20woman's%20request%20to%20terminate%20a%2026-week%20pregnancy%2C%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20DY%20Chandrachud%20asked%20if%20the%20petitioner%20wanted%20permission%20to%20kill%20the%20child%20through%20a%20court%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20asked%20the%20woman's%20counsel%20and%20the%20centre's%20lawyer%20to%20speak%20to%20her%20before%20the%20next%20hearing%20tomorrow.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20three-judge%20bench%20led%20by%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20is%20hearing%20the%20married%20woman's%20petition%20for%20permission%20to%20abort%20the%2026-week%20pregnancy.%20A%20mother%20of%20two%2C%20the%20woman%20has%20said%20she%20is%20suffering%20from%20depression%20and%20is%20not%20in%20a%20position%20to%20raise%20a%20third%20child%2C%20emotionally%20or%20financially.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOn%20October%209%2C%20the%20court%20had%20allowed%20her%20to%20proceed%20with%20the%20pregnancy.%20The%20centre%20then%20sought%20a%20recall%20of%20the%20order%2C%20citing%20the%20advice%20of%20a%20panel%20of%20doctors%20at%20AIIMS%20Delhi%20against%20the%20abortion.%20Yesterday%2C%20a%20two-judge%20bench%20of%20Justice%20Hima%20Kohli%20and%20Justice%20BV%20Nagarathna%20gave%20a%20split%20verdict%20in%20the%20matter.%20Following%20this%2C%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India-led%20bench%20took%20up%20the%20matter%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EQuestioning%20why%20the%20woman%20did%20not%20seek%20permission%20for%20abortion%20earlier%2C%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20asked%2C%20%26quot%3BWhat%20was%20she%20doing%20for%2026%20weeks%3F%20She%20already%20has%20two%20children%3F%20Why%20come%20now%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDo%20we%20issue%20an%20order%20for%20the%20child's%20death%20through%20a%20judicial%20ruling%3F%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAppearing%20for%20the%20centre%2C%20Additional%20Solicitor%20General%20Aishwarya%20Bhati%20cited%20the%20doctors'%20report%20that%20says%20the%20situation%20is%20very%20delicate%20and%20sensitive.%20%26quot%3BThe%20child%20is%20ready%20to%20be%20born.%20It%20won't%20be%20right%20to%20abort%20because%20the%20foetus%20shows%20signs%20of%20life.%20The%20order%20to%20abort%20must%20be%20recalled%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Centre's%20lawyer%20said%20the%20petitioner's%20counsel%20has%20cited%20a%20court%20ruling%20in%20a%20rape%20survivor's%20plea%20for%20permission%20to%20abort.%20%26quot%3BShe%20(petitioner)%20is%20no%20rape%20survivor.%20She%20is%20not%20a%20minor.%20What%20was%20she%20doing%20for%2026%20weeks%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20stressed%20that%20the%20baby%20was%20not%20represented%20in%20the%20matter.%20%26quot%3BWe%20have%20to%20look%20into%20the%20rights%20of%20the%20unborn%20child%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20said%20one%20option%20was%20to%20let%20the%20child%20be%20born%2C%20and%20the%20government%20can%20then%20look%20after%20it.%20It%20asked%20the%20woman%20if%20she%20could%20wait%20for%20a%20few%20more%20weeks%20and%20then%20go%20for%20a%20normal%20delivery.%20The%20court%20underlined%20that%20a%20hasty%20delivery%20at%20this%20point%20may%20lead%20to%20deformities%20in%20the%20foetus.%20%26quot%3BIf%20the%20child%20is%20born%20with%20deformities%20now%2C%20no%20one%20will%20want%20to%20adopt%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697105640000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-09%2Fgv8pfg28_supreme-court_625x300_04_September_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fputting-child-to-death-through-court-chief-justice-in-abortion-case-4474156%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20strong%20observations%20while%20hearing%20a%20woman's%20request%20to%20terminate%20a%2026-week%20pregnancy%2C%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20DY%20Chandrachud%20asked%20if%20the%20petitioner%20wanted%20permission%20to%20kill%20the%20child%20through%20a%20court%20order.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fputting-child-to-death-through-court-chief-justice-in-abortion-case-4474156%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fputting-child-to-death-through-court-chief-justice-in-abortion-case-4474156%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fputting-child-to-death-through-court-chief-justice-in-abortion-case-4474156%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22As%20election%20nears%2C%20Polish%20PM%20warns%20of%20'Islamic%20fighters'%20among%20migrants%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697105574000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-104370323%2Cimgsize-32010.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Fas-election-nears-polish-pm-warns-of-islamic-fighters-among-migrants%2Farticleshow%2F104370011.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F104370011.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EPoland's%20prime%20minister%2C%20Mateusz%20Morawiecki%2C